    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-07T17:02:09+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-07T17:02:09+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T07:32:09Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-07T07:32:09Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high-pressure system south of the state will move east on Wednesday allowing an upper trough to bring instability to southern parts of the state during the day, persisting into Thursday. The upper trough will precede a strong cold front that is forecast to move over South Australia later Thursday. A cooler southwest to southerly flow will gradually moderate as a stronger high-pressure system moves in from the west from Friday to be south of the state on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-07T16:58:29+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T07:28:29Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly clear. Slight chance of a shower south of Yunta in the late afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h tending east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the late evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Medium chance of showers south of Yunta, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds northeast to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending northwest to northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h in the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 16 and 21 with daytime temperatures reaching 28 to 37.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:10am to 3:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 8 [Very High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. High chance of showers south of Yunta, most likely in the afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm south of Yunta in the afternoon. Winds northwest to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending west to northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h in the morning then tending southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 19 and 22 with daytime temperatures reaching 33 to 38.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Winds southerly 25 to 40 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 15 and 21 with daytime temperatures reaching 23 to 35.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-11T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds southerly 25 to 40 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 10 and 17 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 26.</text>
